title: Sundeep Sharma Stand-up Comedy -College Fest
tags: #standupcomedy #hindistandupcomedy #sundeepsharma #uttarpradesh|#uttarpradesh|#himachalpradesh|#uttarakhand|#banaras|#varanasi|#collegefest|#collegefestival|#samayraina|#munawarfaruqi|#anubhavsinghbassi|#zakirkhan|#diwali|#deepavali|#comedy
description: I perform at College festivals quite regularly and connect with the young and brilliant minds that will shape up the future of our beloved nation; India/Bharat. As a rule, I reach colleges/universities much before my performance time and like to learn and research about what is going on in those bright and Khurafati minds. I also do it for the selfish reason that it takes me back to my own college days when I was one of the most khurafati young men but also, one of the top debaters in the country. I eat at the college canteens and like to attend their after parties if I am invited, P.S: I am always invited :D This bit is part fact, part fiction, but it definitely covers some hilarious incidents that happened along the journey of me doing college festival shows across the country, if you like this one and share it extesively and comment on this one, I shall make this a series and will come up with more in this series, for that, you will have to call me to your college festival this season. I am shameless and selfish, I want great food, great ambience and great agricultural environment around me :D Enjoy Karo Doston !!Credits: Venue courtesy: The Habitat-Comedy and Music CafeShot by: Dishang Popat, Vivian Castelino Harsh Shah and Karan KundnaniLive sound recording: Yash Rajiv Barse, Siegen MoopnarEditor: AnkitSound mixing and mastering: Sreejith MenonWritten and performed by: Sundeep Sharma Special Thanks: Balraj Ghai and Saurabh Bothra for accomodating my requestsSaurabh Pandey for being my contant buddy.Erica for production help.Alina Ali for thumbnail and content supervision.Ojas Entertainment and Rahul Jaiswal for College ShowsZakir Khan, Anubhav Singh Bassi, Samay Raina and Munawwar for allowing me to use their names. description: In this video we will see how to make brownie recipe in tamil. There are two types of brownies, cakey brownie which is dry and flaky and fudgy brownie which is softer and more chewy. Both brownies are different in their ratios of flour to fat content. For this recipe, we can use either chocolate bars or chocolate morsels. Also, in this recipe we have used egg but we can make an eggless version by substituting eggs with curd/yogurt.#brownie #brownierecipeintamil #brownierecipe Friends, please do try this brownie recipe at home and share it with your friends and family. Also, please do share your feedback about the recipe in the comments below. All the best and happy cooking!Ingredients:150g semi sweet chocolate or dark chocolate50g Nuts or chocolate1/2 cup Butter (100g)3 Eggs1.5 cup Sugar (300g)1/4 cup Oil1 tsp Vanilla extract1 cup Maida (125 g)1/2 cup cocoa powder (40g)1/8 tsp Salt8 inch square baking pan 175c/350f for 28 min
